  "Compounding 12 times per year": "每年复合12次",
  "Continuous compounding is the mathematical limit of compounding infinitely often. It uses the formula A = Pe^(rt), where e ≈ 2.718, and represents the maximum possible growth from a given interest rate.": "连续复变是无限复变的数学极限。 它使用公式 A = Pe( rt) , 即 e   2. 718 , 代表特定利率的最大可能增长 。",
  "What does 'future value' mean in compound interest?": "未来价值对复合利息意味着什么?",
  "The original amount invested according to conventional analysis": "根据常规分析作出的原投资额",
  "The amount of interest only when evaluated systematically": "仅在系统评估时利息额",
  "The interest rate, particularly regarding both according to": "利率,特别是根据",
  "The total amount of money after interest has been applied over a period of time": "在一段时期内适用了利息之后的金额总额",
  "Future value (A in the formula) is the total amount of money that will be in the account after a specified time, including both the original principal and all accumulated interest.": "未来价值(公式中为A)是指在特定时间之后,包括原始本金和所有累计利息在内,在账户中的金额总额。",
  "What does the variable t represent in the compound interest formula?": "复利公式中的变量 t 代表什么?",
  "The number of compounding periods per year": "每年复利期数",
  "The tax rate": "税率",
  "The total interest earned": "所得利息总额",
  "The time in years that the money is invested or borrowed": "资金投资或借款年份的时间",
  "In A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt), the variable t represents the total time in years. It is multiplied by n (compounding periods per year) to give the total number of compounding periods.": "在 A = P(1 + r/n) (nt) 中,变量 t 表示各年的总时间。乘以 n (每年的计算周期) ,以得出复合期的总数。",
  "What is the difference between nominal rate and effective rate?": "名义费率与有效费率之间的差别是什么?",
  "They are always the same, particularly regarding stated based on established principles": "它们总是相同的,特别是在根据既定原则作出的规定方面。",
  "The effective rate is always lower, particularly regarding effective following the established framework": "有效率总是较低,特别是按照既定框架有效",
  "The nominal rate includes compounding effects based on established principles": "名义汇率包括根据既定原则产生的复合效应",
  "The nominal rate is the stated rate, while the effective rate includes the effect of compounding and is always equal to or higher": "名义兑换率为名义兑换率,而实际兑换率包括复合效应,始终等于或高于",
  "The nominal rate is the stated annual interest rate without considering compounding. The effective rate (APY) accounts for compounding and is always equal to or greater than the nominal rate. They are equal only with annual compounding.": "名义利率是表示的年利率,不考虑复利。实际利率(APY)代表复利,总等于或大于名义利率,只相当于年度复利。",
